cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY

Reasoning: 

1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - This paper deals with temporal resolution of documents using language models, which falls under the scope of natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR), both of which are sub-areas of cs.CL. 

2. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper applies techniques from IR to predict dates via language models over a discretized timeline. 

3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses machine learning techniques to predict dates based on temporal cues implicit in the text. 

4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper's approach of predicting dates solely based on text can be seen as an application of AI techniques to NLP. 

5. cs.CY (Computers and Society) - The paper's findings have implications for the study of history and society, as it enables dating of texts without relying on external temporal extraction resources.
